FBIS4-19008 "drweu071__a94015" FBIS-WEU-94-071-A Daily Report 13 April 1994 ANNEX Germany Kohl Thanks FDP for Statement on Continuing Coalition Kohl Thanks FDP for Statement on Continuing Coalition AU1204122494 Hamburg DPA in German 1117 GMT 12 Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU1204122494 Hamburg DPA German BFN [Excerpt] Bonn (DPA) -- Christian Democratic Union Chairman [CDU] and Federal Chancellor Helmut Kohl expressly thanked the Free Democratic Party on Tuesday [12 April] for the intention expressed the previous day to continue the coalition with the CDU/Christian Social Union after the Bundestag election. In the first coalition talks after the Easter recess, Kohl noticed a considerable improvement in the atmosphere. The "spirit of friendly cooperation" will lead to a success of the coalition parties in the Bundestag election, Kohl was quoted by participants in the talks. [passage omitted]
